NOTE ON DATA AND DERIVED CONTENT:

This MIT license covers the source code in `src/` and `tests/`.

The contents of `data/` (rule corpora, extracted texts, attribution notes)
have separate provenance and licensing — see `data/README.md` for details.

In short:

  - The distilled rule statements in `data/eis/EIS_MASTER_RULES.md` and
    `src/music_rules/data/rules_combined.json` (EIS portion) are paraphrased
    summaries of Spud Murphy's Equal Interval System as taught by Ted Greene
    (1977-1978 lesson notes) plus public web supplements. Quotations are
    short (<15 words) and attributed.

  - The Fux portion of the rule corpus is a Python re-implementation guided
    by FuxCP5 (https://github.com/TomLaiUCL/FuxCP5, GPL-licensed C++ +
    Common Lisp source). No FuxCP5 code is copied verbatim. See
    `data/fux/FuxCP5_attribution.md`.

  - Raw extracted text from Ted Greene's PDFs lives in
    `data/eis/extracted/` for development reference only and is NOT
    redistributed in the published wheel (see `pyproject.toml` excludes).
